<subsection>
<title>Summary of Algebraic Properties</title>
Let <m>a,b</m>, and <m>c</m> represent real numbers, variables, or algebraic expressions. Then the following properties hold:
<table>
	<tabular>
		<row>
		<cell>Commutative Property of Multiplication:</cell>   
		<cell><m>a\cdot b=b\cdot a</m></cell>   
		</row>
		<row>
		<cell>Associative Property of Multiplication:</cell>   
		<cell><m>a\cdot(b\cdot c)=(a\cdot b)\cdot c</m></cell>   
		</row>
		<row>
		<cell>Commutative Property of Addition:</cell>   
		<cell><m>a+b=b+a</m></cell>   
		</row>
		<row>
		<cell>Associative Property of Addition:</cell>   
		<cell><m>a+(b+c)=(a+b)+c</m></cell>   
		</row>
		<row>
		<cell>Distributive Property</cell>   
		<cell><m>a(b+c)=ab+ac</m></cell>   
		</row>
	</tabular>
</table>

